cage
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a crude transporter bridge over some back-country rivers, consisting usu. of a wire cage, suspended from wires, which can be drawn from one side of the river to the other, and back.
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: 1950 N.C.C. Small : used by trampers and hunters 1954 R. Mason `Still in use.'
